        "content": "<p>I'm trying to show that a function that satisfies the below relationships has a root at <code>± I</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">example</span>  <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">ℂ</span> <span class=\"bp\">→</span> <span class=\"n\">ℂ</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n         <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f_one_div</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">z</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"n\">z</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">z</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n         <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f_neg</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">z</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">z</span><span class=\"o\">))</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">I</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"mi\">0</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span>\n   <span class=\"k\">let</span> <span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">I</span>\n   <span class=\"k\">have</span> <span class=\"n\">one_div</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"n\">I</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">*</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"bp\">/</span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span> <span class=\"c1\">--why does `rw [f_one_div]` or `rw [f_one_div I]` not work here???</span>\n   <span class=\"k\">have</span> <span class=\"n\">neg</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">I</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span> <span class=\"c1\">-- ditto</span>\n   <span class=\"k\">have</span> <span class=\"n\">neg_ab</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span> <span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"n\">ℂ</span> <span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"bp\">-</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"n\">b</span> <span class=\"o\">:=</span> <span class=\"kd\">by</span> <span class=\"n\">ring_nf</span>\n   <span class=\"n\">conv_lhs</span> <span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span>\n      <span class=\"n\">rw</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">one_div</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n      <span class=\"n\">simp</span>\n      <span class=\"n\">rw</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">neg_ab</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n      <span class=\"n\">rw</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">neg</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n       <span class=\"c1\">-- here state is `⊢ -I* f I = 0`</span>\n   <span class=\"c1\">-- rough rest of logic is</span>\n   <span class=\"c1\">-- `1 * a = -I * a → (a = 0) ∨ (1 = -I)`</span>\n   <span class=\"c1\">-- `(a = 0) ∨ false`</span>\n   <span class=\"c1\">-- `a = 0`</span>\n   <span class=\"gr\">sorry</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Silly question: why does <code>rw [f_one_div]</code> etc not work? it seems to work when it is a <code>theorem</code> (for a specific <code>f</code>).<br>\nActual question: how do I show <code>a = 0</code> following the sketch of the commented out proof above?</p>",
